#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:7
msgid "This tutorial gives a brief hands-on demonstration of the Delta-glider's atmospheric autopilot."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:14
msgid "\n\nThe autopilot can be programmed via the Script MFD.\nYou should see the terminal in the display at the lower left of the window. If it doesn't show, terminate the simulation and make sure that the \"LuaMFD\" module is activated."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:22
msgid "First, we set the target airspeed. Press the MFD button labelled 'INP' and type the following text into the input box:\n\naap.spd(300)\n\n(aap.spd is the airspeed autopilot, and 300 is the target speed in m/s)\n\nPress Enter to submit the command."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:26
msgid "Good. The glider now fires its main engines and starts to roll. At a ground speed of 100m/s, pull the stick to rotate."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:32
msgid "Excellent. Now raise the gear. Either simply press the \"G\" key, or enter the following into the MFD:\n\nV:Gear(UP)\n\n(note the capital 'V'. Terminal input is case-sensitive.)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:39
msgid "Now, let's set target altitude. Enter the following text in the MFD:\n\naap.alt(10e3)\n\n(This sets the target altitude to 10km.)\n\nMake sure you don't crash into the ground while programming the autopilot!"
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:44
msgid "As we approach the target altitude, the autopilot levels out the climb angle."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:49
msgid "You can reset the target speed simply by entering a new value. Enter the following in the MFD:\n\naap.spd(600)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:54
msgid "Reaching the new target speed. The same mechanism works for resetting the target altitude. Enter this in the MFD:\n\naap.alt(20e3)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:59
msgid "The autopilot only controls the main engines. However, if you engage the glider's scram engines manually, the main engines will be throttled down automatically to maintain the target speed.\n\nTry it by setting the scram engines with [Alt]-[+] and [Alt]-[-] (The Alt key and the + and - keys on the numeric keypad)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:64
msgid "You can manually override the autopilot settings.\nPull the stick to climb to 25km."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:69
msgid "\nNow release the stick to allow the autopilot to return to its target altitude."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:75
msgid "Certain combinations of speed and altitude cannot be sustained by the glider. Try resetting the target speed back to 250 m/s.\n(Turn off scram engines if still engaged)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:79
msgid "The autopilot pitches up in an attempt to maintain the target altitude."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:84
msgid "Eventually, even with fully extended elevator, the glider can't maintain an altitude of 20km at a speed of 250m/s.\nIt sinks until the denser air produces sufficient lift to balance the gravitational force."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:88
msgid "This concludes the tutorial. If you want, stay in the air and experiment with the autopilot settings."
msgstr ""

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Script/Demos/AtmAutopilot.lua:94
msgid "If you want to find out more details about the atmospheric autopilot, type:\n\nhelp(dg_aap)\n\ninto the MFD. This will bring up a help page."
msgstr ""

